Reviews.ReviewText: Lovely restaurant and atmosphere , although I wasnt happy with a particular dish they changed it with no problems .Definitely go again!

Replies.Message: Hey Look I replied again but forgot to include my name somehow.
Seems odd that there would be a reply to a rating-only review, but then here we are.

Reviews.ReviewText: The place is suitable and good for the numbers of tables available as the area is quite big and anyway it maintains a decorous ambiance with a high flair style and standards.

I booked a table at Mango tree restaurant, for my wife's birthday, before the theatre, which was  conveniently 5 mins walk from the restaurant. Ambience of the Mango tree was relaxing & attentiveness of staff was good. The good choice of Thai food was welcomed, as 1st time to a Thai restaurant. Cocktails were great & reasonably priced. Good sized portions, starters & mains. Open table discount was welcomed, as prices were a little expensive. Overall a very good restaurant, which we'll visit again.
Absolutely Great! The Service and hospitality is fantastic and the atmosphere is friendly.

We haven't been to the Mango Tree for a little while. It was as we remembered, great range of cocktails, well presented food and efficient service. A bustling, busy and vibrant atmosphere - maybe not the privacy for a quiet romantic dinner but great for groups, lively conversation and celebrations.

Will continue to go there.

Being quite hesitant about Thai cuisine..I was actually surprised that i enjoyed it. Abit pricey but ambience and food along with service makes it worth while. Will defo recommend to friends and family. Staff were very friendly-  First time I have ever done a review, Which says a lot about this place! Thoroughly enjoyed my food and evening.
Good food @ good value with Open Table discount.

good location, nice food...great deal
think we would be less inclined if the deal was not on, as menu prices are too high relatively
It was a really lovely authentic meal that we would like to visit again not long too long.

Delicious food. The coconut rice is a fantastic compliment to any meal. It seemed very cold temperature-wise  however. I believe there was a problem with plumbing etc in the building on the Sunday we visited so it may have been a temporary glitch.
We returned with some friends and found the food and service excellent. It was their first visit but definitely not their last.

I booked this place for my boyfriends birthday meal.. And from the get go the staff were lovely! The food and general vibe was good too! I would deffo recommend this place to anyone who's planning a special evening with loved ones.

Reviews.RestaurantComment: Just a quick message to say thank you for the food and service, food was amazing. You have a very friendly set of staff from entrance, to the bar, and our waitress Esther she was excellent, me and my colleague we had a good laugh with her and she was very attentive and accommodated to our needs. Thank you.
Reviews.ReviewText: Food was great the vibe was very nice, but what stood out to me was the great customer service from the staff, in particular Esther who served me and my colleague, she was very attentive and was very genuine we had a good laugh. Definitely would go back!!!
Great authentic food nice atmosphere nice place to have a relaxing  meal
Overall good value for MK EY, quality customer service, good ambience. Would be nice to have more vegetarian options.

We had a fantastic night, staff were attentive, ambience was great, food was tasty. The only two negatives were the price of the dishes and the table next to us was very close. Overall a happy and romantic meal.

As always, excellent food, service and great value when getting the open table offer of 50% off.  Best thai food I've ever tasted.  Cocktails are great too!!  Thanks for a fab date night with my boyfriend.
The service was really bad. Food took ages to arrive and they wanted us to pay more for exceeding the 2hour table turn around. Nice ambience though

A lovely restaurant, from entry to table the decor and floral detail is really eyecatching. Our waiter was very attentive and the sommelier has some great recomendations at all price levels. Our starters where a little slow to arrive but the presentation was exceptional and the taste was divine. Main course was delivered swiftly - the rice portions are rather large for one person however - would recommend to share if it's a possibility. 
I was a little disappointed that during main course we were asked if we wanted to order desert as the kitchen was closing - we hadn't caused any delays so I strongly feel the kitchen should stay open until our meal had run its course especially as the final bill was over 330 for 5 people. We were also offered final drinks after desert was offered as the bar was closing - we were still eating on both occasions.
This wouldn't put me off going again as it was a really great experience, and I am happy to recommend the restaurant on the quality of the food served.
Brilliant food and service. Staff treat you like family. Brought out free cake for my girlfriend on her birthday.
Very nice and my wife enjoyed it very much

A good evening meal using the 50% discount offer. They have rearranged their menu to make the offer easier to apply which is good. Wine is expensive (make sure to flick further through the wine list as they start with the very expensive 'fine wines').

We went here on a 1st date, i wasn't too keen on the dress code was very casual  and there was children dining so late at night. The food was ok, i wouldn't rush to go back however the staff and service was lovely - they definitely make the restaurant.

Service was excellent and the place itself is lovely. For starters we had Tom yum which was delicious but fairly small. My fiance had BBQ pork which was yummy. The mains were a huge disappointment, we had minced beef with Thai basil and seafood with noodles. Not very authentic and the flavours were disappointing.

As always, Mango Tree delivered the goods. Service is always very good, not too pushy just perfectly present. The food was great, both presentation and taste wise. And my company were happy with the vegan suggestions, and what was served as well.

Loved it... it was mine and my wifes anniversary and i just sent a message asking if there is anything they can do. They said to let the waitress know and they can put happy anniversary on the desert. I totally forgot but since j walked it they were twlling us happy anniversary and they remember about the desert and made an extra effort to make us feel special. Wife loved it

I have been to Mango tree several times. They have changed the menu for better and I can say the food was even better, we couldn't fault it! It was beautifully presented and very tasty. The service was excellent too. I fully recommend it.

Great service, great food, great atmosphere.

Servers offered some great recommendations for food and wine, would definitely go back.

Reviews.RestaurantComment:
Waiting staff were wonderful. A class. Its a good looking restaurant.
Food was disappointing. Starters- okay. No real reason to cost so much for so little.
The lobster- their most expensive dish came out cold! No flavour, chewy and rough. Tasteless.
Green chick curry- regular takeaway quality or worse. Chicken was firm and overcooked. Curry tasted like dessert.
We paid a lot of money to have bad tasting food. Cant see why we should return.
Reviews.ReviewText:
Waiting staff were wonderful. A class.
Food was disappointing. Starters- okay. No real reason to cost so much for so little.
The lobster- their most expensive dish came out cold! No flavour, chewy and rough. Tasteless.
Green chick curry- regular takeaway quality or worse. Chicken was firm and overcooked. Curry tasted like dessert.
We paid a lot of money to have bad tasting food. Cant see why we should return.

Food was really good with brilliant atmosphere. Cocktails were amazing however service was slow. 
Would def go again.

My experiences here( of which there have been many) have always been amazing, which is why I was very disappointed by this visit.
On arrival, I was told to take a seat in the bar and I would be called when the table was ready. I informed the hostess that my table was now for 3 and not 4. All of my guests arrived by 8.30 but I was not called to my table. I enquires twice and by 8.45 we were still not seated. I asked again and the hostess asked if the table was for 3 or 4, I reminded her it was for 3 and then we were seated at 8.55pm.  As we sat down we were asked if we wanted water, we responded tap water would be fine. We had to ask a further 3 times, we were then told only when we order food would we be given water. Outrageous ! Eventually we received some water and ordered food and wine.  When the food arrived it was stone cold, except for the rice. We asked for it to be be warmed up but when it arrived it was still cold, very little difference. By this point we were very hungry and it was almost 10pm. The food was great, as I remember it, delicious.
The manager came and  apologised and offered us a fruit plate on the house. 
I am not sure if the management has changed but I will not be coming back here again, which is a shame as the food is great but service needs some work.
Had a wonderful evening with my friends and would recommend

Reviews.RestaurantComment: Boyd is the only professional member of staff we had all evening. The bar staff definitely shouldn't be watching and giggling at near naked women acting suggestively in pop videos on the screen above the bar (it's not an over 18 club in Soho for goodness sake! There were families dining). Also the staff should know enough English so they don't mess up orders when you explain what you want clearly.
Reviews.ReviewText:
The food is very good but only some of the service. It took three women at the front desk a while to find my name when I arrived. We chose to have a cocktail in the bar where we were met with an annoyingly pushy drinks waiter recommending us drinks whilst we were trying to read the drinks menu, when he overheard us discussing drinks he'd rudely interrupt. There was a widescreen TV above the bar playing random adverts and a music channel with a very sexual pop video playing that two of the male bar men were watching and having a chat and giggle about. Very unprofessional.

Our waitress who took our food order was good. As there were vegetarians at our table we were offered some spicy peanuts as well as the usual prawn crackers, the peanuts were to be eaten before the meal, these never arrived, we reminded our other waitress (who bought/removed our plates) and she bought out MORE prawn crackers! Not a great start for the vegetarians in our group.  The peanuts arrived half way through our starter and only after we had reminded the waitress who took our order!

We wanted to order more drinks, our plate bringing/removing waitress couldn't understand what we were talking about when we mentioned the names of the cocktails and said something about fish?! We hd to call back our order taking waitress to get the drinks ordered. 

Another thing, they play the most awful bass booming music, feels like you're eating thai food in a night club. One member of our group had to tell a supervisor (Boyd) who then apologised and dealt with the issue right away.

The food is good but we can get similar food, better service and a feeling we're in an authentic thai restaurant elsewhere - there wasn't many Thai staff in the Mango Tree and it felt like you could've been in any type of restaurant - Italian, Indian, French, etc. it didn't feel authentic enough to be a Thai restaurant. I don't know where the management are but they need to return, look at the above issues and train their staff.

Reviews.RestaurantComment: Your sommelier is way too pushy and his grasp if English does not include the word NO. He could not accept that I did not want his help - I almost left because of it.
Reviews.ReviewText: Great Thai food at an over inflated price with really pushy sommelier.
Looks nice but food very average and extremely expensive. Dissappointed with the evening.
The food was absolutely delicious and we got the pre-theatre menu, which was an amazing deal for the excellent food quality.

Reviews.RestaurantComment: The prawns on my main course where very disappointing the texture was not right.  It was the prawn stir fry in Oyster sauce.  Was disappointed to be so quickly told that the 50% offer did not stand as we were just 10 minutes late for our reservation due to traffic.
Reviews.ReviewText: Was disappointed on arrival that as we was 10 minutes late for our reservation we could not have the 50% offer.  I can not fault the service but the food was just not worth the money the prawns in my main course where not real prawns as was in my starter for the price you pay I will not be going back.
Eaten here a few times- food is always a good standard. Waiting staff friendly and efficient.
excellent as always, very good food and superb service

superb food and service,
good large restaurant
one of my favourites in London
A treat for my friends birthday. She loved it. Thank you!

Reviews.RestaurantComment:
Came Saturday 24th around 8pm
Waitress geena was lovely
Reviews.ReviewText: Service amazing, from the moment I walked in, Staff polite and friendly. Even when we were really understanding and accommodating
Great value with the 50% off open table offer and lovely food

Enjoyable evening - food was good but not amazing.  Staff were helpful.  In a couple of the dishes too.much sauce drowned other ingredients.  Other restaurants  are more innovative.  Worth a visit if you are staying locally but consider other restaurants rather than making a special trip.

Mango Tree always delivers great food and outstanding customer service!
Highly recommend it...

I had not been to the Mango Tree for quite a while, but it's still a gem in a bit of desert in terms of decent restaurants near Victoria. Good food - esp the starters which were v generous. Lovely presentation and v good wine list. Had to send the sticky rice back, but in general a good spot. Service was v friendly,  and helped us to get to the theatre in time.

Reviews.RestaurantComment:
We were given a window table as it was our anniversary. A large group nearby had loads of very young children who were getting tired and grumpy, so it wasn't the romantic atmosphere we had hoped for. The layout doesn't help give the place a romantic feel either, more like school canteen arrangement.

The menu is quite deceptive as items appear subtly different on different pages with big price differences - so watch out.

What we had was nice enough, but at 162 this did not seem like good value. Any local Thai restaurant would be as good for half the money.

They gave us a lovely chocolate bomb to share as it was our anniversary which was a nice touch. 

We both asked for jasmine tea and where somewhat surprised when 2 pots of tea were delivered. One would have been sufficient and it seemed like another good way of making you spend more than necessary.

We booked through open table so got 25% off the food bill (certain dishes only) but the 12.5% service charge was more than the discount we got!

Sorry, but overall disappointed sums it up.

Sorry, but overall disappointed sums it up.

Really disappointing place. The food was mediocre at best, service slow, incredibly noisy and unwelcoming atmosphere. Everything about the marketing and pricing suggests upscale dining but is was in fact a fast food experience

I haven't been to Mango Tree for a while and I think it was better now than then.  The vegetable spring rolls were great and a good portion for a starter.  The duck was just how I like it not rare and properly cooked but very succulent!  I will definitely consider returning.

Reviews.RestaurantComment: Thanks again for a wonderful time, your staff are all amazingly friendly and helpful. Keep up the great service!
Reviews.ReviewText: Great food, wonderful ambience and friendly service. What more can one say!

Mango Tree is a well-established Thai restaurant on the the edge of Belgravia but not charging astronomical prices considering the locale. The food is some of the best Thai I have ever tasted and I can wholeheartedly recommend the crab dishes. Also caters for vegetarians and my partner has visited on a number of occasions because of this and had never been disappointed. The service is low-key but efficient and the staff are very welcoming. All in all, a great experience and I plan to return.

Excellent food and service. I have been to Mango Tree a few times and have been very impressed not only with the quality of the food, but also the service. Fernanda looked after us this time and made us feel very welcome. The ambience in the bar and the main restaurant was vibrant and inviting.  We enjoyed the Mango Tree sharing platter, and had seafood in our main courses (Pad Thai King Prawn, and Steamed Sea bass). We'll definitely return and recommend it to others.

The people are very nice. I chose this restaurant because I have been to the same restaurant in Hong Kong, and therefore I knew that the food would not be too bad.  It turns out that I was right, but the price to me has been set too high compared to the dollar's worth.

Was a brilliant date with the wife. Restaurant was fairly quiet for Saturday lunchtime. I emailed to change reservation and they quickly responded. Food got served fairly quickly, service was on point and food was absolutely delicious. I had the steak with stir fried noodles. Wow just wow. The shrimp popcorn was tasty, and a starter that had chicken wrapped in leaves. Overall a lovely place albeit expensive.

I visited Mango tree for my birthday dinner. The atmosphere was nice, the table we were placed was nice. The service was very slow. We kept having to ask for top of of water etc The food came out cold, I was disappointed to say the least. The price wasn't too bad. Overall it's a nice place maybe to visit for drinks but for food I'm not too sure based solely on my experience on that day.
Great meal and service
Food was absolutely fantastic and service was amazing. Highly recommend eating here and I would definitely go again.
Excellent service with delicious food. 2nd time I've been here and will be coming more.  Staff know how to take care of you. The mojito drinks are lovely

Reviews.RestaurantComment: Your staff are excellent and my partner and I love dining with you, however the food (and the Thai Martini) was just way too spicy. The air conditioning seemed not to be working (properly) either, ant it was quite a hot day, so we had to keep stepping out of the restaurant and ordering lots of water to cool down from all the chillies. We had the Opentable set menu - it was deliscious.... I think
Reviews.ReviewText: Wonderful ambience, very attentive staff, good prices, however, the food was WAY too spicy. Every dish seemed to be extra spicy, which took away from the great(?) taste of authentic Thai food. Even the Thai martini was too spicy :-o! Next time I go there I must remember to request the chef to hold on the chillies! Other then that - amazing experience!
The food is terrific (love the Tom Sum)! However we waited at least 15 min trying to find a waitress to check out
Foods are disgusting. The quality of foods has become really bad compared to two years ago when I last visited the restaurant.

Reviews.RestaurantComment: From start to end there was no flaw, I came here to celebrate my mums birthday and we were both in love! We were greeted with such a warm welcome from the door Hostess' who offered to take our coats and seated us down. She also checked with us are these seats ok! I have NEVER been asked that, it was such a nice touch and difference from the potential excuse me can we sit over there please! We were very happy with the seats anyway! Our waiter Hector was so friendly and sweet, from start to end! Ester who served our meals was very kind also and everyone was so attentive to our table. The food was delicious I really loved everything I ordered and I had 3 courses!! - Their Chef is amazing! Thank you to the Kitchen team! Everything was so perfect and I only asked for a happy birthday message with dessert we order but I wasn't expecting a huge sparkler candle and the waiters singing happy birthday to my mum. I was overwhelmed by how lovely everyone was and how special they made the day! Boyd the manager (i think) was our sweet cherry on top who took my mothers dessert off the bill as a birthday gift! - SO LOVELY! As if they had not done enough already with everything else. Highly recommend you spend a special occasion here. Small groups I think are nicer and better suited to the atmosphere. Not ideal for BIG parties unless they offer private rooms which would be perfect. Thank you so much!

Highly recommend you spend a special occasion here. Small groups I think are nicer and better suited to the atmosphere. Not ideal for BIG parties unless they offer private rooms which would be perfect.
Food was lovely if not a bit on the spicy side. Attentive staff but felt a bit impersonal.

The menus are complicated as you cannot order whatever you like as there are so many restrictions and the most boring of the dishes only are included in the offer. We chose from various menus and we were disappointed. The dim sum platter had 5 pieces , one of each for 17 making each one come in at 3.50 literally a mouthful only! The other dishes were not as good as we are used to getting at the Mango tree. The red chicken curry was nothing special. The duck was tasteless served on a bit of green pak choi and the mixed seafood was very spicy. No comments were made by the staff as to how spicy the dishes were  or not. I have been going to the Mango tree since it opened and I won't be going there again. It certainly has lost its individulaity and quality of service and food and is just like any local high street take away now.

We went to the Mango Tree for the first time and it was wonderful. The staff were excellent and very attentive without being overly so. The food was excellent. We chose a starter and a main dish each from the A La Carte menu and it was superb. I would recommend it to anyone who loves Thai/Asian food. We look forward to the next time.
Lovely evening spent at Mango Tree.  Good food, excellent service for our anniversary.
Great time slow service
Great location and decor

I've been a regular at Mango Tree for over 5 years it's good to see the quality hasn't changed, and the 50% makes it more reasonable.
The duck curry in the pineapple is always a favourite as is the Prawn Pad Thai.  The other curries though seem a little too sweet it could do with a bit more spice.
Cocktails are lovely and beautiful restaurant.  It seemed to take far too long to bring out our birthday cake however we then realised they had prepared a special dessert on the house to bring along, very sweet gesture.
Will surely see me again soon!
It was my husband's birthday meal, and the staff were extremely friendly,  and even bought a mini cake out with candles and his name. Really nice touch and my husband had a great birthday. Thank you

I went to the mango tree to celebrate a friend's birthday. The food was good and the 50% discount was very good value for money. We ordered the Thai fish cakes (very good) , vegetable spring rolls and the talay pad cha (spicy wok-fried seafood - this was spicy!). The only thing that could of been better was the staff could of remembered to write happy birthday on the dessert plate as requested, but not a big thing!
Lovely lunch!

Having moved from southeast Asia, I've found it very difficult to find a good, authentic Thai restaurant in Central London. Though pricey and (in my case) saved for special occasions, Mango Tree really hit the mark. One thing that really stood out was the spice levels - I asked for extra extra chilli and they really delivered, the Thai way, whereas in many other restaurants, 'spicy' food doesn't really turn out spicy. The herbs and flavours they used were really authentic and I was impressed! Only downside is that the staff, very slightly, gave off that boastful vibe (not quite pretentious but a little bit I'm-too-busy-for-you), which many people don't mind but something I noticed. Further, the restaurant was fantastically spacious with really high ceilings - it almost feels like your table is secluded - but the decoration was a little dry and the layout and lighting wasn't used wisely to create a good ambience for dinner-time in the summer (i.e. it was too bright and I didn't feel like I was dining at a high-end Asian-inspired restaurant). However, the food trumped all and I would definitely go again!!!

despite 25% discount for booking through Open Table and ignoring the 3 bottles of wine, the food portions were ridiculously small, particularly the main courses. To say they were poor value for money is an understatement. 
We were a party of 4 and I don't have a big appetite so I had just enough to eat but my husband still felt hungry even though we ordered 4 starters and 4 main courses plus rice. 
I didn't like the rice being served from a small polythene bag! Never seen this before even having lived in Hong Kong for many years and travelling in the Far East extensively.
I've had lunch twice at this restaurant and it was far better than dinner. Dinner wasn't just disappointing it was a rip off. The food quality was good and the lamb shank particularly good.
The waiters couldn't top up the wine fast enough and didn't ask if I wanted more (which I didn't!). Too pushy.
Great ambiance. Food was only ok.

Reviews.RestaurantComment: I would like to thank Olga for looking after us so well on this our first visit.
Reviews.ReviewText: Our first visit using the 50% discounted a la carte menu and will certainly be back again.
Good food, great service. There was also love music on the Thursday night that we attended so I enjoyed it.
It was my daughters birthday. Staff were very attentive and foot good. We even sat next to JLS
Nice restaurant and atmosphere, good food. Very expansive

Reviews.RestaurantComment: Our waitress Esther was excellent.  Just love coming to Mango Tree.  Visited on 26 July for my son Sameers birthday and you really surprised him with a lovely cake and candle.  On the 9th August I visited again with friends and just love your papaya salad , pad Thai and veg green curry.  Thank you to Esther for suggesting the mango rice pudding dessert .  Thank you to Sandra for suggesting open table for booking and discount code
Reviews.ReviewText: I just love Mango Tree, it was my second visit in a week.  The food is amazing with really good quality unique vegetarian dishes.  The papaya salad is out of this world, full of flavour and zest.   Each dish has unusual flavours and textures.  The fresh mango rice pudding with coconut cream was so delicious.  The service was superb.  Our waitress was Esther and she really looked after us and gave us superb service.  Sandra looked after my booking  time changes.  Thankyou to Mango Tree and all staff.
Here is a restaurant in need of serious TLC.It looks tired and faded, and the food is distinctly average. It is not pricey, but I would pay more if the food was better.
Amazing experience, really good service and would highly recommend.

Spent an enjoyable evening unwinding at the Mango Tree with a friend. Started in the bar with a Caribbean Kiss - a lethally great cocktail,  and later moved on to dinner. 
 
The food, as always was full of wonderful and subtle flavours and artistically served by very attentive and friendly staff throughout the evening.

The  live music was a plus and added to the ambience. Specials, like the fifty percent off on the a la carte menus is noteworthy. Found the wine listing a bit expensive but still affordable.

In all, a thoroughly relaxed evening in great surroundings.

The service was fantastic from the start to finish. The staff were very attentive and polite.
Helped us with our menu choices etc. We came here as vegetarians there was a decent choice and no fish sauce added to the vegetarian food.
One of our favourite eating places in London. Anyone who like Thai food should put this at the top of their places to try. Not cheap but exceptional food and a great venue.
Love this place, t green curry always cooked to perfection
Love this place, the food is great and the service is prompt.
An enjoyable meal in a busy and vibrant environment. Service was excellent and staff helpful and friendly.
Excellent dinner with friends...great special offer! Really good service and delicious food.

We have been to Mango Tree many times and it never disappoints. The food and service are excellent. I personally wouldn't eat there without the open-table discount as then it would end up being quite pricey. With the discount it is still not cheap, but we always walk away feeling very satisfied, happy and full!

Everything about my birthday evening at Mango Tree was fantastic. The welcoming staff, waiting staff, drink recommendations, dining experience and restaurant decor/table layout were all brilliant. The food was delicious, very flavoursome and good portions.
I recommend everyone to try Mango Tree atleast once.

Reviews.RestaurantComment: Came here on the 28th July for our 20th Annivesary. We love Thai food & you were recommended to us & I must say we was not disappointed. The food was great (better than the blue elephant ) service was quick & the staff serving us were so friendly & helpful. Thank you for giving us a wonderful 1st experience
Reviews.ReviewText: Went for our anniversary & had a wonderful evening. The food was fantastic & the staff friendly & service was on point. Would go back for sure.
Nice food and very polite professional service.

easy booking system through Open Table - pleasant staff on arrival
above average Thai food - a little pricey
gets noisy once the place fills up
we will be back ......

Reviews.RestaurantComment: My family and I came to your restaurant on Thursday last week (21st July) to celebrate my Mum's 60th birthday. We had such a lovely time. Thank you for making it extra special for us with your amazing customer service and professionalism. Thank you Muriela and Ester (and the others whose names I can't remember). I will definitely come again.
Reviews.ReviewText: Lovely customer service. My family and I went there to celebrate my Mum's 60th birthday. They were brilliant!! Muriela and Ester are the only names I can remember now but they were all wonderful. The food and the ambience were also spot on.

One of our worst dining experiences in London with awful service and barely ok food. 

Beware of booking the  50% offer as the actual discount was less than 20%

Would not recommend it to a friend and won't be going back.

I have been to the Mango Tree before and was not disappointed this time either. The food was very good. The restaurant was very busy as it was a Saturday evening and, therefore, service was a bit slow but this did not detract from our evening. Our American guests were very impressed. I shall go again.
